          <div class="col-md-4"><img style="max-height:200px" class="img-responsive center-block" src="/assets/viator.png" alt="Viator Package Tour to Patagonia"><br><h5>Or how about two weeks in Patagonia with Viator? It will run you more than $1,500! Using Patagonia On A Budget you can visit all the exact same sites for less than $400, leaving you an extra $1,100 to spend on your trip!<h5></div>
          <div class="col-md-4"><img style="max-height:200px"  class="img-responsive center-block" src="/assets/adventuretour.png" alt="Wildlife Tour to Patagonia"><br><h5>Even if you're just headed to Torres del Paine National Park, Adventure Life will charge you an absurd $1,900. Instead, I'll walk you through the details and information you need to replicate this itinerary for less than $200!</h5></div>
        </div>

      <h3>What about guide books?</h3>

      <p>Usually, guide books can be great resources for planning itineraries, finding the best places to stay in each town, and finding some adventure.<p> 

      <p>But even picking up a guide book for Patagonia might have you shuddering. The cheapest hostel in town is $25/night? Guide books are written for all kinds of travelers; they mention expensive hotels and the most famous sights, but ignore the best options for backpackers and budget travelers. Plus many guides are outdated. Enormous inflation has caused prices to triple or quadruple since the most recent version, so you can't rely on the information anymore.</p>

      <p>Add in all of these factors and you might end up frustrated by the planning process and just succumbing to a package tour.</p>

      <p>I get it. Planning a trip to Patagonia can be a challenge. That's why I wrote Patagonia On A Budget. </p>

      <h3>What if I told you traveling in Patagonia can cost just $30/day?</h3>

      <p>This book is written by someone who really did it. I traveled for 3 months in Patagonia, spending an average of $26/day without missing out on any of the top sights.</p>

      <p>In this book, I'll teach you everything you need to know to make your dream vacation to Patagonia a reality. You'll learn the best value for accommodation in each town, the most spectacular things to do, and the tactics you need to keep it all under budget.</p>

      <p>Best of all, these are the REAL PRICES, researched and personally experienced by real backpackers. This book only makes recommendations based on the best value, not because I am sponsored by any corporations.</p>

      <p>Patagonia On A Budget will thoroughly prepare you for life on the road, help you navigate while traveling, remove barriers, and provide information simply not available anywhere else. Ready for your adventure? Let's dive in...</p>
